	<sect1 id="intro">
		<title>Introduction to &application;</title>
			<para>
				Imagination is a lightweight DVD slide show creator developed in C with the GTK+2 toolkit and Cairo. Imagination is designed to be
				be fast and easy-to-use. Its user interface is clean and intuitive, and does not include any confusing or useless options by default.
				It requires the ffmpeg encoder to produce the movie file and libsox to import the audio files. Yes you don't need any other third-party software!
			</para>
	</sect1>
	<sect1 id="window">
		<title>Imagination's window</title>
		<para>
			This section describes the sections of the Imagination's window.
		</para>
		<sect2 id="toolbar">
			<title>Toolbar</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><para>New</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Open</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Save</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Save As</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Close</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Properties</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Preview</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Export</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Quit</para></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
			<sect3 id="toolbar_new">
				<title>New</title>
				<para>
					This menu allows you to create a new slideshow. The slideshow dialog is displayed. You can choose the video format (PAL/NTSC), if to scale the picture so that it covers the whole screen avoiding the black stripes and the background color to be displayed when the picture is too small and the rescaling doesn't succed to cover the whole screen. You can also change these options later.
				</para>
			</sect3>
			<sect3 id="toolbar_open">
				<title>Open</title>
				<para>
					This menu allows you to open a previously saved slideshow.
				</para>
			</sect3>
		</sect2>
		<sect2 id="image_area">
			<title>Image Area</title>
			<para>Cucu</para>
		</sect2>
		<sect2 id="Side Panel">
			<title>Side Panel</title>
			<para>Please refer to the Working Area section of this document for a detailed explanation.</para>
		</sect2>
		<sect2 id="status_bar">
			<title>Status Bar</title>
			<para>Cucu</para>
		</sect2>		
	</sect1>			
	<sect1 id="menu">
		<title>Imagination's menus</title>
		<para>
			This section describes in detail the menus of Imagination.
		</para>
		<sect2 id="slideshow">
			<title>Slideshow menu</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><para>New</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Open</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Save</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Save As</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Close</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Properties</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Preview</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Export</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Quit</para></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
			<sect3 id="new">
				<title>New</title>
				<para>
					This menu allows you to create a new slideshow. The slideshow dialog is displayed. You can choose the video format (PAL/NTSC), if to scale the picture so that it covers the whole screen avoiding the black stripes and the background color to be displayed when the picture is too small and the rescaling doesn't succed to cover the whole screen. You can also change these options later.
				</para>
			</sect3>
			<sect3 id="open">
				<title>Open</title>
				<para>
					This menu allows you to open a previously saved slideshow.
				</para>
			</sect3>
			<sect3 id="save">
				<title>Save</title>
				<para>
					This menu allows you to save a previously saved slideshow. The filename won't be asked.
				</para>
			</sect3>
			<sect3 id="saveas">
				<title>Save as</title>
				<para>
					This menu allows you save a slideshow with a different filename.
				</para>
			</sect3>
			<sect3 id="close">
				<title>Close</title>
				<para>
					This menu closes the slideshow. If the slideshow is not saved yet or you changed something Imagination will ask you to save it first.
				</para>
			</sect3>
			<sect3 id="properties">
				<title>Properties</title>
				<para>
					This menu displays a dialog with the slideshow properties. Please see above for an explanation of the available settings.
				</para>
			</sect3>
			<sect3 id="preview_slideshow">
				<title>Preview</title>
				<para>
					This menu starts the preview of the slideshow in the image area. If you want to start the preview by a specific slide just select it by left-clicking on it. The preview quality if affected by the setting in the menu <menuchoice><guimenu>Slide</guimenu><guimenuitem>Preview quality</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.
				</para>
			</sect3>
			<sect3 id="export">
				<title>Export</title>
				<para>
					This submenu allows you to export the slideshow in three different formats: VOB (DVD Video) OGV (Ogg Theora/Vorbis) and FLV (Flash Video).
				</para>
			</sect3>
			<sect3 id="quit">
				<title>Quit</title>
				<para>
					This menu quits Imagination. If the slideshow wasn't saved yet Imagination will prompt you to save it first.
				</para>
			</sect3>
		</sect2>
		<sect2 id="slide">
			<title>Slide menu</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><para>Import pictures</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Import music</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Delete</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Preview quality</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Rotate clockwise</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Rotate counter-clockwise</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Zoom</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Select all</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Unselect all</para></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
			<sect3 id="import_pictures">
				<title>Import pictures</title>
				<para>
					This menu opens up a file dialog allowing you to choose the pictures to import in Imagination To select more than one pictures press and hold SHIFT key while clicking on the files. A progress bar is displayed in the status bar notifying you the percentage progress of the pictures' import.
				</para>
			</sect3>
			<sect3 id="import_music">
				<title>Import music</title>
				<para>
					This is the same as the previous only but works for audio files. Please make sure you have installed the package <citetitle>libsox-fmt-all</citetitle> otherwise you won't be able to import MP3 files.
				</para>
			</sect3>
			<sect3 id="delete">
				<title>Delete</title>
				<para>
					This deletes the selected slides. Hold down the SHIFT key to select more than one slide at once.
				</para>
			</sect3>
			<sect3 id="preview">
				<title>Preview</title>
				<para>
					This submenu allows you to set different quality for the
					preview and the image quality in the image area. This option
					doesn't affect exported video in any way. It's main purpose
					is to speed-up the creation process, since loading large
					images from disk at original size may take some time
					(loading of 4032x3024 image from disk takes cca. 2s on
					modern system).
				</para>
			</sect3>
		</sect2>
		<sect2 id="help">
			<title>Help menu</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><para>Contents</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>About</para></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</sect2>
	</sect1>
	<sect1 id="working_area">
		<title>Working Area</title>
		<para>
			This section explains the slide settings located on the Imagination window's side panel.
		</para>
		<sect2 id="working_area_tools">
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><para>Slide Settings</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Slide Motion</para></listitem>
				<listitem><para>Slide Text</para></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
			<sect3 id="slide_settings">
				<title>Slide Settings</title>
				<para>
					This section allows you to choose a random transition or to pick one from the drop-down menu. You can set the transition speed choosing among Fast, Normal and Slow and the time in seconds that the slide must remain still. Finally you can see the total time length of the slideshow. Note: the slide (or the slides) must be selected for this section to work.
				</para>
			</sect3>
			<sect3 id="slide_motion">
				<title>Slide Motion</title>
				<para>
					This section allows you to apply the famous Ken Burns effects on a slide. Just begin by clicking on the Add button to add a stop point. Then use the Zoom slider to zoom in or out and then hold the left mouse button on the picture to center a detail of the picture. If you commit a mistake re-adjust your slide and then click the Update button. You can add as many stop points as you want. The Remove button deletes a stop point. Click the preview button on the toolbar or choose <menuchoice><guimenu>Slideshow</guimenu><guimenuitem>Preview</guimenuitem></menuchoice> to have a preview of the effect. Note: the slide (or the slides) must be selected for this section to work. 
				</para>
			</sect3>
			<sect3 id="slide_text">
				<title>Slide Text</title>
				<para>
					This section bla bla bla.
				</para>
			</sect3>
		</sect2>
	</sect1>
